Certainly! Here’s a JSON data example for the application without the user entity while retaining the other relevant entities and their workflows:

### JSON Data Example

```json
{
  "deployments": [
    {
      "id": "1",
      "type": "cyoda-env",
      "status": "running",
      "build_id": "12345",
      "repository_url": "http://example.com/repo.git",
      "properties": {
        "user_defined_keyspace": "example_namespace",
        "user_defined_namespace": "example_namespace"
      },
      "statistics": {
        "duration": "120s",
        "success_rate": "100%",
        "data_transferred": "5GB"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "type": "user_app",
      "status": "success",
      "build_id": "67890",
      "repository_url": "http://example.com/repo.git",
      "is_public": true,
      "statistics": {
        "duration": "60s",
        "success_rate": "100%",
        "data_transferred": "1GB"
      }
    }
  ],
  "workflows": [
    {
      "name": "Deployment Workflow",
      "transitions": [
        {
          "name": "Start Deployment",
          "from_state": "idle",
          "to_state": "running",
          "processor": "start_deployment_processor"
        },
        {
          "name": "Complete Deployment",
          "from_state": "running",
          "to_state": "success",
          "processor": "complete_deployment_processor"
        },
        {
          "name": "Fail Deployment",
          "from_state": "running",
          "to_state": "failed",
          "processor": "fail_deployment_processor"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Cancel User Application Deployment",
      "transitions": [
        {
          "name": "Cancel",
          "from_state": "running",
          "to_state": "canceled",
          "processor": "cancel_user_app_processor"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

### Explanation
- The **"deployments"** array contains entities for different types of deployments (environment and user application).
- Each deployment has relevant properties, status, build ID, and execution statistics.
- The **"workflows"** array defines workflow transitions along with processors that can be invoked during the transitions.

Feel free to modify any of the information or structure as needed for your application's requirements!
